### Project: tether — Phases 2-4 Complete (#354-362, plus bug fixes #340-345, #364-365)

**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/tether
**Final stats:** 152 tests, 14 source files, mypy --strict + pyright strict = 0 errors

#### Phase 2 (Tasks #354-356)
- `_screen.py`: ANSI escape stripping (strip_ansi, has_ansi) — fixed OSC regex ordering (] overlaps single-char ESC)
- `_interact.py`: Standalone interact function with input/output filters
- `_run.py`: High-level run() with events, env, withexitstatus support
- Updated `__init__.py` public API with new exports
- 25 new tests (test_screen, test_run, test_spawn_advanced)

#### Phase 3 (Tasks #357-359)
- `_async.py`: AsyncSpawn with native async/await — no deprecated @asyncio.coroutine
  - Fixed _on_readable future guard for EOF handling (fut.done() check)
  - Uses asyncio.get_running_loop().add_reader() for PTY fd
  - asyncio.shield() to prevent wait_for cancelling the reader future
- `_popen.py`: PopenSpawn for non-PTY pipe-based interaction via subprocess.Popen
- `_ssh.py`: SSHSession built on Spawn with login/prompt/run/logout
- Replaced stub classes in __init__.py with real imports
- 30 new tests (test_async: 9, test_popen: 11, test_ssh: 10)

#### Phase 4 (Tasks #360-362)
- `_compat.py` + `compat.py`: pexpect compatibility shim (spawn, run, EOF, TIMEOUT, pxssh, ExceptionPexpect)
- 18 compat tests including 10 cross-verification vs real pexpect
- pyright strict: 0 errors (added PtyProcess.exitstatus/signalstatus properties, cleaned up private access)
- Benchmarks: tether is 3.6–95× faster than pexpect (bench_tether.py, RESULTS.md)
- CI: updated to uv + astral-sh/setup-uv, Python 3.10-3.13 on ubuntu+macos, fail-fast: false
- pyproject.toml: Development Status Beta, pexpect as dev dependency
- README.md: full API reference, pexpect migration guide, benchmark table
- CHANGELOG.md: v0.1.0 entry with features, bug fixes, performance

